<TITLE> Fire guts 300 shanties in Ctg's Bastuhara colony </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Chittagong, Feb 27 (bdnews24.com)  A fire broke out at the Bastuhara colony in Baklia, Chittagong on Saturday, gutting 300 shanties on the embankment alongside Shah Amanat Bridge. Fire service and Baklia police said the fire originated from a stove at a tea stall beside the colony on the embankment around 11:30 am on Saturday and spread rapidly through the shanties. Two firemen sustained injuries fighting the fire and were admitted to Chittagong Medical College Hospital. Assistant director of the Agrabad fire service, Nurul Haque told bdnews24.com, "Initial investigation revealed that nearly 300 shanties were completely gutted and property worth Tk 30 lakhs were destroyed." He continued, "13 fire fighting vehicles rushed to the location and brought the fire under control by 2:30pm." "No reports of casualties, other than the two firemen injured in the fire were received", said the fire official. Baklia Police Station in-charge Shihab Uddin told bdnews24.com, "Workers of various professions and refugees stays at the Bastuhara Colony. Initial probe revealed that 300 shanties were burnt in the fire." He also mentioned that no reports of death or missing persons were filed in the incident. Various political organisations are backing the illegally-built colony on the embankment along the Karnafuli river. 
